message.content: It is not possible to provide an accurate summary of what most women in Macedonia think of divorce as opinions on this matter can vary greatly among individuals. Women's perspectives on divorce in Macedonia, as in any other country, are influenced by various factors such as personal experiences, cultural and religious beliefs, education, and societal norms. Some women may view divorce as a viable option to escape an unhappy or abusive marriage, while others may prioritize maintaining the stability of their family unit and may be more hesitant to consider divorce. It is important to recognize that women's opinions on divorce are diverse and can differ significantly from person to person.
